HEADWORD: Uppish
<hw>Up"pish</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[From
<er>Up</er>.]</ety> <def>Proud; arrogant; assuming; putting on airs of
superiority.</def> <mark>[Colloq.]</mark> <au>T. Brown.</au> --
<wordforms><wf>Up"pish*ly</wf>, <pos>adv.</pos> <mark>[Colloq.]</mark>
-- <wf>Up"pish*ness</wf>, <pos>n.</pos>
<mark>[Colloq.]</mark></wordforms>⟦br⟧
